Analysis of Deviance Table
 Cox model: response is  Surv(rep(1, 4070L), case_)

Model 1: ~ Elevation + Aspect + Slope + Lodge_dist + sl_ * (Elevation + Aspect + Slope + Lodge_dist) + log(sl_) * (Elevation + Aspect + Slope + Lodge_dist) + cos(ta_) * (Elevation + Aspect + Slope + Lodge_dist) + strata(step_id_)
 Model 2: ~ Elevation + Aspect + Slope + Lodge_dist + sl_ + log(sl_) + cos(ta_) + strata(step_id_)

#The p-value of >0.05, indicates that the difference between the two models is not statistically significant and model 2 is an adequate fit of the data. The additional complexity provided by model 1 does not improve the model's fit.
